===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|bʰleh₁|id=blow}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{der|en|fro|inflation||swelling}}, from {{der|en|la|īnflātiō||expansion", "blowing up}}, from {{m|la|īnflātus}}, the perfect passive participle of {{m|la|īnflō||blow into, expand}}, from {{m|la|in||into}} + {{m|la|flō||blow}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪnˈfleɪʃən/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|eɪʃən|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# An act, instance of, or state of [[expansion]] or increase in [[size]], especially by [[injection]] of a [[gas]].
#: ''The '''inflation''' of the balloon took five hours.''
# {{lb|en|economics}} An increase in the general level of prices or in the [[cost of living]].
# {{lb|en|economics}} A decline in the value of [[money]].
# {{lb|en|economics}} An increase in the quantity of [[money]], leading to a devaluation of existing money.
# Undue expansion or increase, as of academic grades.
# {{lb|en|cosmology}} An extremely rapid expansion of the universe, theorised to have occurred very shortly after the [[big bang]].

